ra_pages" somehow. Is it some<br />system tool that does that automatically, and if so based on what,<br />exactly?<br /><br />I'm also slightly worried about the fact that now the max read-ahead<br />may actually be zero, and/or basically infinite (there's a ioctl to<br />set it that only tests that it's not negative). Does everything react<br />ok to that?<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
